cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.CL 

The paper deals with unsupervised representation learning from images and videos, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of current artificial data augmentation techniques and proposes the use of videos as a natural source of augmentation, which relates to the fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on a variety of tasks, including object recognition and semantic segmentation, which are common topics in natural language processing (cs.CL).
